00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:03,640
The treacherous chancellor said...

560
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:04,680
I heard everything.

561
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:06,990
There's going to be
a tea banquet in the palace.

562
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,640
This is a chance.

563
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:09,860
When that happens,

564
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:11,680
I'll find an excuse
to go to Lan Boutique

565
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,440
and meet Qing in person.

566
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:15,680
But

567
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:18,120
you have to stay by his side that day.

568
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,480
What if there's no chance?

569
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,880
I'll find another chance then.

570
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,560
I'm a spy.

571
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:25,920
I should take the risk.

572
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,790
Have a piece of pastry
to wash out the bitterness.

573
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:36,520
They are Beiyuan's cake.

574
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,200
You have to wait in line

575
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:39,680
a long time to get

576
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:40,640
their pastries.

577
00:39:40,660 --> 00:39:41,860
Guess he's not that heartless.

578
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:03,440
Lady Jiang
has been recovering well recently.

579
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:04,400
Don't worry.

580
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:10,280
Don't call her Lady Jiang anymore.

581
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,640
What should I call her?

582
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,640
She's the princess of Beiyuan.

583
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:16,640
You should call her "Your Highness"

584
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:18,040
like Qingtai.

585
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:19,520
Yes.

586
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:55,490
♪The flower bloomed,
knowing nothing at all♪

587
00:40:55,490 --> 00:40:58,520
♪In splendor, proud and tall♪

588
00:40:59,430 --> 00:41:02,660
♪The flower fell, lashed by the wind♪

589
00:41:02,660 --> 00:41:06,420
♪In a daze,
it felt like lifetimes had thinned♪

590
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:09,900
♪Petals soaked in rain♪

591
00:41:09,900 --> 00:41:13,240
♪Heartbreak follows again and again♪

592
00:41:13,620 --> 00:41:17,290
♪The flower weeps, burdened by thoughts♪

593
00:41:17,290 --> 00:41:23,010
♪With no one it can be brought♪

594
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:34,890
♪Wishes struggle through the mire♪

595
00:41:35,300 --> 00:41:42,140
♪Regrets clash in hopeless fire♪

596
00:41:42,650 --> 00:41:49,650
♪Still I hope she'll pick the flower
kissed by dew♪

597
00:41:49,950 --> 00:41:54,100
♪Even if it means this flower♪

598
00:41:54,100 --> 00:42:01,070
♪Will be hers to give to someone new♪

599
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:15,400
♪Whose eyes
did the flower's heart meet?♪

600
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:18,650
♪Love and hate held back, discreet♪

601
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:22,780
♪The flower withers, feelings in decay♪

602
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:29,360
♪No longer needing to say♪

603
00:42:33,420 --> 00:42:40,360
♪Yet I still long for her in madness♪

604
00:42:40,750 --> 00:42:47,720
♪Unafraid of judgment or sadness♪

605
00:42:48,060 --> 00:42:55,060
♪Remembering the words
she spoke of flowers and skies♪

606
00:42:55,430 --> 00:42:57,200
♪And finding♪

607
00:42:57,200 --> 00:43:06,200
♪They were her gentle heart's reply♪